stylometry: Our group product used an @RISK simulation to find the appropriate server quanitity at Applebee's during their peak time of 5:30-7:30 to maximize profit by decreasing waiting cost. We did this problem because several of our group members were in the serving profession and we found it to be a problem we could relate to. As a manager at a restaurant currently, I have noticed that many times, incorrect numbers of servers, whetehr above or below the proper amount, are scheduled at the wrong time. It demoralizes employees when they don't bring home money or show up for a shift and are sent home right away. Server income is based upon a percentage of tips based on sales numbers, and the better and more even the sales numbers are, the happier the employees. I learned that although it may seem like less is better from a servering standpoint, from a managerial standpoint, it is better to have more staff on hand and just send them home. In order to keep every one happy and ultimately the customer, we need to compromise and determine the right number, which can be determined through a simulation model such as @RISK.
